(- Scalability: memory does not collapse under long-term accumulation) Tj
T*
(- Personalization: memory captures what the user feels, not just what they said) Tj
T*
(- Security: memory is resistant to manipulation and corruption) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Without these, long-term memory systems often become:) Tj
T*
(- noisy) Tj
T*
(- stale) Tj
T*
(- unsafe) Tj
T*
(- hard to trust) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Best real-world use cases) Tj
T*
(This architecture is especially useful for:) Tj
T*
(- personal AI assistants with long-lived user memory) Tj
T*
(- coding agents that remember user coding style and preferences) Tj
T*
(- tutoring agents that track confidence, likes, dislikes, and learning history) Tj
T*
(- healthcare or support agents where important facts must persist and be protected) Tj
T*
(- autonomous workflow agents that need stable memory across sessions) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Short version) Tj
T*
(The project's real value is this:) Tj
T*
(- pruning keeps memory useful as it grows) Tj
T*
(- sentiment makes memory human-aware) Tj
T*
(- poisoning defense makes memory trustworthy) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Together, they move an agent from storing chat history to maintaining long-term, relevant,) Tj
T*
(emotionally aware, and secure memory.) Tj
T*
() Tj
ET
